Import data

# Get data
demo <- readr::read_rds('./data/demographics.rds')

Sample size

# Sample size by study site
demo %>%
    group_by(Site) %>%
    summarise(count = n()) %>%
    knitr::kable(., caption = 'Sample size by study site')
Sample size by study site
Site count
r1 47
r2 49
u1 47
u2 17 
# Sample size by study site and intervention group
demo %>%
    group_by(Site, Group) %>%
    summarise(count = n()) %>%
    group_by(Site) %>%
    mutate(sum = sum(count)) %>%
    mutate(percent = round(count / sum * 100, 1)) %>%
    select(-sum) %>%
    knitr::kable(., caption = 'Sample size by intervention group at each study site')
Sample size by intervention group at each study site
Site Group count percent
r1 p 28 59.6
r1 t 19 40.4
r2 p 26 53.1
r2 t 23 46.9
u1 p 24 51.1
u1 t 23 48.9
u2 p 10 58.8
u2 t 7 41.2

Sex

# Sex by study site
demo %>%
    group_by(Site, Sex) %>%
    summarise(count = n()) %>%
    group_by(Site) %>%
    mutate(sum = sum(count)) %>%
    mutate(percent = round(count / sum * 100, 1)) %>%
    select(-sum) %>%
    knitr::kable(., caption = 'Sex by study site')
Sex by study site
Site Sex count percent
r1 male 47 100
r2 female 49 100
u1 female 31 66
u1 male 16 34
u2 female 17 100 
# Sex by study site and intervention group
demo %>%
    group_by(Site, Group, Sex) %>%
    summarise(count = n()) %>%
    group_by(Site) %>%
    mutate(sum = sum(count)) %>%
    mutate(percent = round(count / sum * 100, 1)) %>%
    select(-sum) %>%
    knitr::kable(., caption = 'Sex by intervention group at each study site')

Age

# Age by study site
demo %>%
    group_by(Site) %>%
    summarise(mean = round(mean(Age), 1),
              sd = round(sd(Age), 1),
              range = paste0(round(min(Age), 2), ' - ', 
                             round(max(Age), 2))) %>%
    knitr::kable(., caption = 'Age (years) by study site')
Age (years) by study site
Site mean sd range
r1 35.3 3.0 28 - 40
r2 32.9 4.6 18 - 40
u1 39.3 6.3 27 - 58
u2 30.4 4.8 23 - 37 
# Age by study site and intervention group
demo %>%
    group_by(Site, Group) %>%
    summarise(mean = round(mean(Age), 1),
              sd = round(sd(Age), 1),
              range = paste0(round(min(Age), 2), ' - ', 
                             round(max(Age), 2))) %>%
    knitr::kable(., caption = 'Age (years) by intervention group at each study site')
Age (years) by intervention group at each study site
Site Group mean sd range
r1 p 35.6 2.7 31 - 40
r1 t 34.7 3.4 28 - 40
r2 p 33.3 5.0 18 - 40
r2 t 32.4 4.2 23 - 40
u1 p 39.1 7.1 27 - 58
u1 t 39.6 5.4 30 - 49
u2 p 29.1 5.3 23 - 37
u2 t 32.3 3.5 26 - 36 
# Plot
## Age plotted according to study site and intervention group
ggplot(data = demo) +
    aes(y = Age,
        x = Site,
        colour = Group,
        fill = Group) +
    geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.6) +
    labs(title = 'Age in years',
         subtitle = 'According to study site and intervention group')

First recorded CD4

# First CD4 by study site
demo %>%
    group_by(Site) %>%
    summarise(median = round(median(CD4, na.rm = TRUE)),
              IQR = paste0(round(quantile(CD4, prob = 0.25, na.rm = TRUE)), ' - ', 
                           round(quantile(CD4, prob = 0.75, na.rm = TRUE)))) %>%
    knitr::kable(., caption = 'First recorded CD4 (cells/ul) by study site')

SOS health literacy

  • lhl: low health literacy
  • hl: health literate
# Health literacy by study site
demo %>%
    group_by(Site, SOS_mnemonic) %>%
    summarise(count = n()) %>%
    group_by(Site) %>%
    mutate(sum = sum(count)) %>%
    mutate(percent = round(count / sum * 100, 1)) %>%
    select(-sum) %>%
    knitr::kable(., caption = 'SOS health literacy by study site')

# Plot
## Years of education plotted according to study site
ggplot(data = demo) +
    aes(x = Years_education,
        fill = Site) +
    geom_bar() +
    facet_grid(Site ~ .) +
    labs(title = 'Years of education', 
         substitle = 'Faceted by study site') +
    theme(legend.position = 'none')
